FBIS4-40224 "drsov115_i_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-115 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 CENTRAL ASIA Kazakhstan Industrial Output in Semipalatinsk Declines 30 Percent Industrial Output in Semipalatinsk Declines 30 Percent LD1506124294 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0100 GMT 15 Jun 94 LD1506124294 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network Kazakh BFN [Text] This year, under various pretexts, over 60 industrial enterprises in Semipalatinsk Oblast have come to a standstill. Over 20,000 workers have lost their jobs. In addition, small businesses, with a total work force of over 3,500 workers, have also discontinued work. Over 20 other enterprises of the oblast, which employ a total of about 6,500 people, are working half days. The oblast's industrial output has declined by 30 percent, as compared with last year.
